{"quote": "Hen to pan", "page_title": "Monism", "page_bio": "Monism is a philosophical and cosmological stance which posits an ultimate Unity of all things, and that all apparent differences, distinctions, divisions and separations are ultimately only apparent or partial aspects of an ultimate whole. It has arisen and developed with many diverse forms of emphasis, in widely diverse and distinct philosophical, mystical, religious and scientific traditions, and is a primary element of most forms of Perennial philosophy.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monism"}